Implement git integration for chipper start and chipper done.

`chipper start <id>`:
- Commit the manifest update (chipper-queue)
- Create and checkout a branch named <PROJECT>-<slug> (e.g. CHP-login)
- If branch_prefix is set in .chipper, use <prefix>/<PROJECT>-<slug> (e.g. feat/CHP-login)

`chipper done <id>`:
- Commit the ticket file (with AI summary) and updated chipper-queue
- Prompt user whether to push the branch

Git integration is enabled by default when inside a git repository.
It can be disabled globally with `git = false` in .chipper,
or per-command with the --no-git flag.

Depends on: cli-scaffolding, manifest-implementation, status-commands
